  <title>LECTURER/SENIOR LECTURER, DEPARTMENT OF MANAGEMENT (Contract Position)</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/lecturersenior-lecturer-department-management-contract-position</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;LECTURER/SENIOR LECTURER, DEPARTMENT OF MANAGEMENT (Contract Position)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;mfetane&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Tue, 22/08/2023 - 12:02&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Management&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Thu, 14 Sep. 2023&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF BUSINESS - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF MANAGEMENT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW" xml:lang="EN-ZW"&gt;&lt;span&gt;IRC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;1102 - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;LECTURER/SENIOR LECTURER &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(Contract Position)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Faculty of Business invites applications from suitably qualified persons for the post of lecturer in Management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to: (i) Teach Management courses to undergraduate and graduate students.  The candidate must have demonstrable capacity to teach at least three of the following areas: Business Mathematics, Quantitative Methods for Business, Research Methods, Project Management, Strategic Management, diversity management, cross cultural management, managing in a global business environment, managing at the top echelon of the organisation, or any other related management courses.  The department reserves the right to allocate other courses in addition to those outlined above. (ii) Supervise students' research projects, thesis and dissertations at both undergraduate and graduate levels; (iii) Supervise students in internship (iv)&lt;span&gt; Participate in all academic and professional service activities of the department as well as community service, normally associated with a University lectureship; (v) the successful candidate will be expected to conduct research in his/her area of expertise. (vi) &lt;/span&gt;Undertake any other duties as may be assigned by the Head of Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The requirements for appointment at each rank are as follows:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lecturer:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have (i) a PhD in Management or related fields; (ii) &lt;span&gt;Master's degree in Management &lt;/span&gt;or related fields, (iii) evidence of engagement in research. The following will be added advantages: (i) evidence of Governance and Social Engagement; (ii) teaching experience at a University or comparable institution preferably in Management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;N.B &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In special circumstances a Masters' degree in Management or related fields &lt;span&gt;with a &lt;/span&gt;Bachelor's degree in Management or related fields of at least 2(i) pass/GPA of at least 3.6 or equivalent may be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Lecturer: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates should: (i) have a Doctoral Degree in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Management&lt;span&gt; or related field; (ii) have at least &lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt; years of teaching experience at a university or comparable institution; (iii) have a good and sustained record of research and publications with at least &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt; research outputs published with recognised publishers, &lt;strong&gt;4 &lt;/strong&gt;of which should be articles in refereed or accredited journals internationally. The remaining &lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt; publications could be journal articles, book chapters, peer reviewed conference proceedings, etc., published by recognised publishers; (v) be the lead and/or single author in at least &lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt; journal publications, (vi) the research publications should reflect an international spread, (vii) demonstrate evidence of governance and social engagement. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The curriculum vitae should contain a detailed list of published works, clearly specifying titles of publications, ISBN numbers (for books, book chapters and conference proceedings),dates of publications, names of publishers, name/s of co-authors if any and number of pages. The works&lt;span&gt; should be categorized into books, book chapters, refereed &lt;/span&gt;journals, non-refereed works, consultancies and practical media projects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: The University of Botswana offers a competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; For more information about the University visit our website: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ub.bw/"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;www.ub.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position.  They should also quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CV’s (including telephone, telefax and email), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;names and addresses of three referees, and send complete documentation to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resource Manager, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Faculty of Business, University of Botswana, Private Bag UB00701, Gaborone, Botswana, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Telephone (267) 355 2231 or 355 5844; Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:fobvacancies@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;fobvacancies@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to: (i) Quote the Vacancy number and position applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the above address, before stipulated closing date. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be processed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to Block 245 Office 233.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 14 September 2023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      </description>
