            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF BUSINESS - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF MANAGEMENT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FB/M   1/2022 - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;PART-TIME TEACHING ASSISTANTS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; The successful candidates will conduct tutorials in the subject areas listed below during the academic year 2022/2023.  They will also be expected to assist the respective course lecturers:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Subject areas:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Organisational Behaviour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Principles of Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Entrepreneurship courses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Business Plan Development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Introduction to Business Mathematics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Quantitative Methods for Business&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Candidates should have a minimum of Bachelor’s degree in Management with at least a 2.1 or equivalent in a business-related field.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants should indicate their availability during the period of 08:00Hrs – 17:00Hrs during which tutorials are normally run. Experience of teaching at a University level will be an added advantage. Applicants should indicate the subjects in which they are competent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;The University of Botswana offers competitive part-time rates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to Apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position.  They should also quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CV’s (including telephone, telefax and email), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;names and addresses of three referees, and send complete documentation to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Human Resource Manager, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;Faculty of Business, University of Botswana, Private Bag UB00701, Gaborone, Botswana, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;Telephone (267) 355 2231 or 355 5844; Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:fobvacancies@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;fobvacancies@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants should inform their referees to: (i) Quote the Vacancy number &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; position applied for &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; (ii) submit their references directly to the above address, before stipulated closing date. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to Block 245 Office 233.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be processed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

